# Python Style and Quality Rules

Follow these conventions and checks across Python files:

- Imports: standard library, third-party, local; keep sorted (ruff I)
- Line length: 120 (see `pyproject.toml` ruff config)
- Type hints: use explicit typing for public APIs; enable strict mypy
- Avoid unused imports and variables; rely on ruff (`E`, `F`, `W`, `I`, `N`, `UP`, `B`, `A`, `C4`, `SIM`, `RET`)
- Prefer early returns; avoid deep nesting; meaningful variable names
- Do not catch broad exceptions; only handle expected errors meaningfully
- Keep comments focused on rationale or tricky edge cases

